# Append-only logbook files.
#
# Two agents (cloud on claude/* branches, local on master) both append handoff
# notes to CLAUDE.md section 6, the HANDOFF-LOG.md history, and rows to the
# COLLAB-PROTOCOL.md work registry. The actual code never collides (each tool is
# its own cmd/ + internal/ dir), but these text files collided on EVERY
# non-fast-forward merge — which is exactly what made the one-click "Get Becky
# Updates" button punt to the assistant once more than one branch was waiting.
#
# git's built-in `union` merge driver resolves an overlapping change by keeping
# BOTH sides' lines instead of raising a conflict. For append-only narrative logs
# that is the correct behaviour: nobody loses a handoff note, and the button can
# merge unattended. (Tradeoff: if both sides edit the *same existing* line, union
# keeps both copies — a visible duplicate a human can trim, never a lost edit.)
# HANDOFF-LOG.md was missing here and collided on 2026-06-27 (two sessions each
# prepended a top entry); adding it makes that auto-resolve like CLAUDE.md §6.
CLAUDE.md            merge=union
COLLAB-PROTOCOL.md   merge=union
HANDOFF-LOG.md       merge=union

# Golden test fixtures must stay LF so byte-compare tests pass on Windows checkouts.
*.golden.md text eol=lf
*.golden text eol=lf
